                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18301209-190-off1066 t18301209-190-crimeloc1069"></join>. On the 25th of November I saw the prisoner take down a handkerchief which was pinned to a gown inside the shop; he was rolling it up - I ran and collared him; I had seen him looking very hard through the window before he took it- this is the handkerchief.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I worked three years and a half for Mr. Osborne - he has not had work for me this mouth - I was looking for work, and saw this handkerchief at the door - I looked at it with an intention of buying it; it came down - I took it up, and was going to put it in the rack when the man took me.</p>
